If you do not speak much Italian but you are hungry for Italian food, you may emerge speaking Italian after an enjoyable meal at II Colosseo Restaurant & Pizza, where the Italian food is delicious. Located in one of New York City’s safer areas on Brooklyn’s dynamic 18th Avenue, shoppers and tourists alike can pop in with or without reservations and enjoy a welcoming staff that strives for the most authentic Italian experience. An extensive menu of pizzas baked in wood-burning ovens and succulent Italian dishes that depart from the usual marinara- sauce-melted-cheese-meatballs formula, so prevalent elsewhere. I tend not to eat seafood but observed many others partaking of II Colosseo’s offerings with gusto. Reasonably priced; the Maitre d’, breadboy, busboy and waiter are all tipped separately. Buon appetito!
The food is spectacular! The wood oven pizza, best Calamari, Carciofi, and stuffed clams! And the best espresso on 18th ave..

I have been struggling to find an Italian restaurant that delivers and provides fresh, homemade, amazing food. Despite there being plenty of options in Brooklyn, I tried many before coming across Il Colosseo. So far, we have ordered pasta fagioli, baked clams, chicken francaise, rigatoni w vodka, fried calamari, and two pies, tiramisu, and cheesecake all for delivery and every time food was exceptionally fresh, delivered on time, and tasted amazing! This is now my go-to spot any time I want Italian!  P.S. This was some of the best vodka sauces I ever tried.
